🧠 OS Concept 1: Deadlock Detection vs Recovery

You learned prevention and avoidance earlier.
Now:

👉 What if deadlock already happened?

🔹 Deadlock Detection

System checks:

“Is deadlock present?”

Often uses resource-allocation graph ideas.

Goal:

👉 identify deadlock.

🔹 Recovery

Once detected:

How do we fix it?

Methods:

Terminate process(es)
Preempt resources
Rollback (restore earlier state)
🧠 Analogy

Detection:

Smoke alarm detects fire 🔥

Recovery:

Firefighting puts it out 🚒

🎯 Interview Trap

Q: Difference between avoidance and detection?

👉 Avoidance prevents unsafe allocation.
👉 Detection finds deadlock after it occurs.

🧠 Memory Trick
Detection = find problem
Recovery = fix problem
🧠 OS Concept 2: Paging vs Swapping

Confusing question 🔥

Paging

Moves pages.

Small units.

Page in
Page out
Swapping

Moves entire process between RAM and disk.

Big unit.

🧠 Analogy

Paging:

Move few book pages.

Swapping:

Move whole book.

Key Difference
Paging	Swapping
Pages	Whole process
Fine-grained	Coarse-grained
🎯 Placement Question

Q: Does virtual memory use paging or swapping?

👉 Primarily paging.

🧠 Memory Trick
Paging = parts
Swapping = whole
⚙️ COA Concept 3: Temporal vs Spatial Locality

Very frequently asked.

Temporal Locality

If data used recently,

👉 likely used again soon.

Example:

for(i=0;i<10;i++)

i reused repeatedly.

Spatial Locality

If one memory location used,

👉 nearby locations likely used.

Example:

arr[0], arr[1], arr[2]
🧠 Analogy

Reading book:

Temporal:

Re-read same paragraph.

Spatial:

Read nearby paragraphs.

🎯 Interview Question

Q: Cache relies on what principle?

👉 Locality of reference (temporal + spatial)

🧠 Memory Trick
Temporal = same again
Spatial = nearby next
⚙️ COA Concept 4: Cache Replacement Policies (LRU vs FIFO)
FIFO

Remove oldest.

Simple.

LRU

Remove least recently used.

Smarter.

Example

Cache:

1 2 3

Need add 4.

FIFO:

remove 1

LRU:

remove least recently used.

🎯 Interview Trap

Q: Why LRU better than FIFO?

👉 It uses usage behavior, FIFO only age.

🔗 Connection

Same idea also used in page replacement.

🧠 Memory Trick
FIFO = oldest out
LRU = coldest out
